The paper proposes a novel learning-based active learning framework that incorporates uncertainty and diversity sampling for optimization. This framework is evaluated on three different classification tasks, including image classification, salary level prediction, and entity resolution. Given the focus on machine learning and optimization techniques for active learning, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
